00:27:46.680 --> 00:27:49.580
The next consideration, be moderate.

00:27:49.840 --> 00:27:55.165
In my experience,
content is added without enough thought.

00:27:55.280 --> 00:27:57.639
This is the case in many times.

00:27:57.640 --> 00:28:02.399
For example, someone might think
that a moving GIF looks cool.

00:28:02.400 --> 00:28:06.839
Consequently, it is included
into the website without checking

00:28:06.840 --> 00:28:10.886
how it affects
the user experience or accessibility.

00:28:12.549 --> 00:28:15.719
While some people
might be impressed by dynamic elements,

00:28:15.720 --> 00:28:18.365
others would find them annoying.

00:28:18.619 --> 00:28:23.279
Trendy websites shouldn't choose
dynamic content just for fun.

00:28:23.280 --> 00:28:27.406
It's there to drive conversion
and share information.

00:28:27.800 --> 00:28:30.000
Here are a few advices.

00:28:30.515 --> 00:28:34.559
Limit parallax scrolling
to one instance per page.

00:28:34.560 --> 00:28:38.200
Keep dynamic elements small and shallow.

00:28:38.865 --> 00:28:41.539
Ensure that it's well-spaced

00:28:41.540 --> 00:28:46.080
from text and this increases readability.

00:28:46.600 --> 00:28:50.519
The good news
is that there are many types of inclusive

00:28:50.520 --> 00:28:54.487
dynamic content that work
well on a trendy website.

00:28:54.560 --> 00:28:58.679
I'm going to list some of them,
divided into four groups.

00:28:58.680 --> 00:29:03.282
Group one, organizing information
elements like drop-downs,

00:29:04.001 --> 00:29:08.639
also known as night show
or accordion components tabs,

00:29:08.640 --> 00:29:14.114
which is a very good component
to make content into a clear structure.

00:29:14.950 --> 00:29:20.583
Tooltips that provide additional
details without overwhelming the users.

00:29:21.120 --> 00:29:24.452
Group two, related
to forms like dialogues,

00:29:24.720 --> 00:29:30.360
auto-suggestions in field,
conditional form fields, combo boxes.

00:29:31.000 --> 00:29:36.599
Group three, related to interaction
like real-time data updates,

00:29:36.600 --> 00:29:38.999
expandable image galleries,

00:29:39.000 --> 00:29:44.160
interactive maps, augmented reality,
interactive sliders.

00:29:44.840 --> 00:29:47.319
Group four is content-related.

00:29:47.680 --> 00:29:53.200
Interactive infographics,
parallax scrolling, infinite scroll.

00:29:54.712 --> 00:30:00.119
Remember that the default use
of these elements is often not accessible,

00:30:00.120 --> 00:30:04.642
but all of them can be used
in a way that suits all users.

00:30:04.760 --> 00:30:09.031
Lastly, dynamic elements
increase cognitive loads.

00:30:09.440 --> 00:30:12.359
This may seem like a minor issue,
but it's not.

00:30:12.360 --> 00:30:14.719
People with reduced cognitive function,

00:30:14.720 --> 00:30:19.199
whether due to a headache,
stress, or a medical condition,

00:30:19.200 --> 00:30:22.136
may find these elements overwhelming.

00:30:28.040 --> 00:30:31.959
Our time is short,
so step into our last domain, targets.

00:30:31.960 --> 00:30:36.600
There are more types as follows,
links within text.

00:30:36.800 --> 00:30:38.999
It's crucial to distinguish links

00:30:39.000 --> 00:30:42.491
from regular text using
more than just color.

00:30:43.200 --> 00:30:45.079
Navigation menu links.

00:30:45.080 --> 00:30:49.680
This often seems easy,
but careful planning is necessary,

00:30:49.840 --> 00:30:52.567
especially for complex megamenus.

00:30:53.400 --> 00:30:59.720
Consistency is key, even when menus
are different in pages or users.

00:31:00.600 --> 00:31:04.920
It's also important to make parent
menus easy to find.

00:31:05.720 --> 00:31:07.880
Application menu buttons.

00:31:08.120 --> 00:31:11.639
Application menus
are different from navigation menus.

00:31:11.640 --> 00:31:14.199
These are typically
associated with actions

00:31:14.200 --> 00:31:20.320
or commands within a web application
like save, open settings, and so on.

00:31:20.880 --> 00:31:22.781
Call to action buttons.

00:31:23.120 --> 00:31:26.279
This typically receives
significant design attention

00:31:26.280 --> 00:31:31.199
and usually meets accessibility
standards with a good contrast.

00:31:31.640 --> 00:31:33.639
Form targets like buttons, sliders,

00:31:33.640 --> 00:31:38.760
switches, auto-suggestions,
inactive buttons, and so on.

00:31:39.760 --> 00:31:45.120
Switches should be designed
so users can easily tell their status.

00:31:45.360 --> 00:31:51.120
Sliders need to display values
when navigated via keyboard.

00:31:52.420 --> 00:31:54.299
Auto-suggestions should have

00:31:54.300 --> 00:31:57.600
a good contrast and be resizable.

00:31:58.480 --> 00:32:02.559
Inactive buttons
don't have a minimum contrast requirement,

00:32:02.560 --> 00:32:05.100
but it's essential

00:32:05.380 --> 00:32:09.900
to clearly differentiate

00:32:09.940 --> 00:32:13.000
between active and inactive states.

00:32:14.196 --> 00:32:17.319
Player control buttons
for interacting with media

00:32:17.320 --> 00:32:23.160
players and special targets
like chessboard or locations.

00:32:23.480 --> 00:32:29.800
Designing special targets
requires specialized expertise.

00:32:30.960 --> 00:32:36.593
These targets need extra care due
to the complexity of user interaction.

00:32:39.680 --> 00:32:41.360
Top considerations.

00:32:41.520 --> 00:32:45.579
The target on a web page
is crucial for user interaction

00:32:45.580 --> 00:32:48.473
and must be available for everyone.

00:32:49.040 --> 00:32:54.011
Landing pages, which drive profits,
are typically very good.

00:32:54.240 --> 00:32:56.519
This is a proof that accessibility

00:32:56.520 --> 00:33:00.680
can directly contribute
to increased revenue.

00:33:01.600 --> 00:33:03.959
Here is a top list of my considerations.

00:33:03.960 --> 00:33:05.639
Proper contrast.

00:33:05.640 --> 00:33:11.035
Make sure that clickable links stand
out from non-clickable elements.

00:33:12.040 --> 00:33:13.479
Visual cues.

00:33:13.480 --> 00:33:18.240
Links should be distinct from non-links
in at least two ways.

00:33:18.360 --> 00:33:20.760
Proper sizing for touch.

00:33:21.000 --> 00:33:25.919
Ensure that clickable areas
are large enough for touch interactions.

00:33:25.920 --> 00:33:28.079
The WCAG recommends a minimum size

00:33:28.080 --> 00:33:32.240
of 24 CSS pixel circles for touch areas,

00:33:34.440 --> 00:33:39.240
but for better usability
aim for an even bigger size.

00:33:40.200 --> 00:33:41.688
Responsiveness.

00:33:42.600 --> 00:33:47.159
Using only four or five different screens

00:33:47.160 --> 00:33:50.359
for simple design might not be enough.

00:33:50.360 --> 00:33:54.159
Sometimes a high-quality fluid
grid can help,

00:33:54.160 --> 00:33:58.000
but you might need
extra adjustments to make sure

00:33:58.142 --> 00:34:02.240
all content and functions
fit well on each viewport,

00:34:03.160 --> 00:34:08.000
and ensure that design
is consistent across different devices.

00:34:09.320 --> 00:34:11.000
Focus indicators.

00:34:11.160 --> 00:34:15.842
Design your site that there is enough
space for focus indicators.

00:34:15.843 --> 00:34:17.799
While you can use different visual cues,

00:34:17.800 --> 00:34:22.560
an outline is often the most practical
and consistent method.

00:34:23.280 --> 00:34:26.440
Clear and simple labeling.

00:34:26.840 --> 00:34:29.927
Use straightforward language for labels.

00:34:29.928 --> 00:34:35.520
While creative wording can be fun,
it may not be clear to everyone.

00:34:35.680 --> 00:34:38.400
For example, instead of saying,

00:34:38.800 --> 00:34:43.560
access restricted to individuals
aged 18 and above,

00:34:43.760 --> 00:34:47.480
simply say, 18 and older only.

00:34:48.400 --> 00:34:51.045
Differentiate links and buttons.

00:34:51.640 --> 00:34:53.879
Links should navigate to other pages,

00:34:53.880 --> 00:34:56.819
while buttons should perform functions.

00:34:56.820 --> 00:35:01.422
Use buttons for sliders, tabs,
or single-page applications.

00:35:07.720 --> 00:35:09.786
Hiding target by default.

00:35:09.960 --> 00:35:13.199
Many times the target appears
when it's hovered.

00:35:13.200 --> 00:35:17.399
In other cases, the target is hidden
by a fixed-position element.

00:35:17.400 --> 00:35:21.879
If targets are hidden,
write a token to instruct developers

00:35:21.880 --> 00:35:25.926
that it should be visible
in case of hover or focus.

00:35:31.800 --> 00:35:34.079
