00:39:39.760 --> 00:39:43.960
technology can include
most of the trendy elements.

00:39:44.280 --> 00:39:47.612
It's important to use
them in a soulful way

00:39:47.840 --> 00:39:50.733
and follow the specific guidelines.

00:39:53.480 --> 00:39:55.463
Here are some resources.

00:39:57.600 --> 00:40:02.959
Smashing Magazine,
and there are very good UX magazines

00:40:02.960 --> 00:40:05.191
dealing with accessibility.

00:40:05.400 --> 00:40:10.180
Understanding success
criteria is a part of a WCAG,

00:40:10.920 --> 00:40:16.580
and each criteria
has understanding section

00:40:17.540 --> 00:40:23.160
with resources, detailed explanations,
examples, and best cases.

00:40:23.586 --> 00:40:28.200
Deque University's comprehensive
learning materials.

00:40:31.280 --> 00:40:36.039
There's other courses on how to design
for accessibility for UX designers.

00:40:36.040 --> 00:40:40.319
I've reviewed many courses,
and I think this is the best.

00:40:40.320 --> 00:40:45.079
Figma, OneGage,
we don't have experience with Figma.

00:40:45.080 --> 00:40:46.879
We don't have experience with OneGage.

00:40:46.880 --> 00:40:50.120
If you have, please let me know.

00:40:51.360 --> 00:40:53.619
Today, Johnny Albert will present

00:40:53.620 --> 00:40:58.279
the inclusive design strategies
for WordPress professionals.

00:40:58.280 --> 00:41:00.459
The last year's Carrie Fisher

00:41:00.460 --> 00:41:03.079
and Jonathan Whiting has
a very good presentation

00:41:03.080 --> 00:41:05.040
about this topic.

00:41:05.760 --> 00:41:09.040
Takeaways very shortly.

00:41:09.160 --> 00:41:15.240
Make accessibility a core part
of your project and don't rely on plugins.

00:41:15.460 --> 00:41:20.720
Two, understand that users
have a wide range of abilities.

00:41:20.800 --> 00:41:24.719
Three, bring in experts
to train your designers

00:41:24.720 --> 00:41:27.117
and give them the best tools.

00:41:28.229 --> 00:41:32.593
Four, if you don't have enough knowledge,
ask an expert.

00:41:33.440 --> 00:41:39.319
I believe that true
accessibility isn't just a quick fix.

00:41:39.320 --> 00:41:42.479
It's a commitment to a thoughtful
and inclusive design.

00:41:42.480 --> 00:41:47.479
It may require more effort upfront,
but the rewards are unmeasurable.

00:41:47.480 --> 00:41:50.759
By creating websites
that everyone can use,

00:41:50.760 --> 00:41:53.119
we are not merely
just following guidelines,

00:41:53.120 --> 00:41:56.240
but building a better web for everyone.

00:41:56.480 --> 00:41:59.259
Thank you for your time,
and thanks to my colleagues

00:41:59.260 --> 00:42:01.799
who helped me
to prepare this presentation.

