00:42:14.880 --> 00:42:18.600
We have a question in the Q&amp;A.

00:42:20.000 --> 00:42:23.639
The question is,
what is one of the most difficult design

00:42:23.640 --> 00:42:28.638
requests you had to make accessible,
and what was your approach?

00:42:32.280 --> 00:42:33.679
<v Zsolt> That's a good question.

00:42:33.680 --> 00:42:36.077
Let's go back to the polling.

00:42:38.880 --> 00:42:42.779
For us, the color part
was the most difficult

00:42:42.833 --> 00:42:49.833
because when we start
to create a new website,

00:42:50.580 --> 00:42:57.559
the designers want very specific colors,

00:42:57.560 --> 00:43:00.959
and it's very difficult to find
those colors

00:43:00.960 --> 00:43:05.320
which have a good contrast
ratio to each other.

00:43:07.440 --> 00:43:09.239
That was the most difficult part.

00:43:09.240 --> 00:43:12.652
I think the other thing
is much more easier.

00:43:15.600 --> 00:43:17.040
Is it okay?

00:43:17.760 --> 00:43:18.851
<v Kelly> Yes.

00:43:21.440 --> 00:43:25.299
Our next question is,
do you have accessible websites

00:43:25.300 --> 00:43:30.319
that you think have great design
that you could share as examples?

00:43:30.320 --> 00:43:34.366
Are there any brands
that you take inspiration from?

00:43:36.400 --> 00:43:38.301
<v Zsolt> Fortunately not.

00:43:39.200 --> 00:43:42.532
There are many good accessible web design.

00:43:48.240 --> 00:43:52.920
I would say that, for example,
in Hungary, I don't know.

00:43:53.627 --> 00:43:58.719
There are two webshops
which has a very accessible web design.

00:43:58.720 --> 00:44:03.900
One of them made
the accessibility redesign

00:44:04.380 --> 00:44:09.099
in five years' time, and after,

00:44:09.100 --> 00:44:13.479
it announced that three and a half times

00:44:13.480 --> 00:44:19.280
more users are buying

00:44:19.281 --> 00:44:21.029
from this webshop.

00:44:21.720 --> 00:44:25.079
I don't want to say
the name of this website,

00:44:25.080 --> 00:44:27.279
because it's an international company.

00:44:27.280 --> 00:44:32.360
It's a quite good webshop,
accessible, trendy, very good.

00:44:32.800 --> 00:44:38.520
I also like Google's accessibility.

00:44:39.800 --> 00:44:42.219
Most of the Google applications

00:44:42.220 --> 00:44:47.599
can be quite good design,

00:44:47.600 --> 00:44:50.280
and they are also accessible.

00:44:54.120 --> 00:44:57.770
<v Kelly> We have maybe
one or two questions here.

00:44:57.800 --> 00:45:02.119
The next one is,
if you have to do a major brand redesign,

00:45:02.120 --> 00:45:06.484
what element of accessibility
would you implement first,

00:45:06.520 --> 00:45:09.082
and what is the most important?

00:45:10.640 --> 00:45:14.686
<v Zsolt> Sorry to say,
but there is no most important.

00:45:17.160 --> 00:45:20.199
Accessibility is not
very difficult for me,

00:45:20.200 --> 00:45:22.499
but I think it's quite complex

00:45:22.500 --> 00:45:28.679
because we the experts can see

00:45:28.680 --> 00:45:34.559
that many different users
have many different abilities,

00:45:34.560 --> 00:45:38.280
and we are doing an accessible website.

00:45:38.892 --> 00:45:44.520
We can sync all of them, and we find
a solution which fits all of them.

00:45:44.782 --> 00:45:46.419
There is no most important

00:45:46.420 --> 00:45:52.359
because everyone is important.

00:45:52.360 --> 00:45:56.059
Maybe you can rank the most important

00:45:56.060 --> 00:45:59.399
as this is blocking for some people,

00:45:59.400 --> 00:46:02.039
and this is not blocking for some people.

00:46:02.040 --> 00:46:04.420
For example, if you have

00:46:05.780 --> 00:46:12.040
an unlabeled target, an unlabeled button,

00:46:12.600 --> 00:46:15.079
it can be blocking
for screen reader users,

00:46:15.080 --> 00:46:19.840
for many other people,
for voice recognition, software users.

00:46:19.880 --> 00:46:21.759
This is a blocking element.

00:46:21.760 --> 00:46:24.359
If you have a color contrast not enough,

00:46:24.360 --> 00:46:28.406
maybe a little bit less,
this is not a blocking one.

00:46:28.880 --> 00:46:35.780
I think accessibility is collecting
all of this information together

00:46:35.820 --> 00:46:39.960
and putting it into
the one trendy solution.

